title: Concerti per Mandolini - Paisiello - Giuliani - Lecce
description:
Concerti per Mandolini
Paisiello - Giuliani - Lecce

This is a very nice, hard-to-find recording of concertos by three lesser-known Italian classical composers.  
Please help seed so that others may enjoy it as well.

Ugo Orlandi, mandolin
Jodi Levitz, viola
Dorina Frati, second mandolin

I Solisiti Veneti
Director:  Claudio Scimone

Label:  Erato
Recorded:  May - June, 1985 at Villa Contarini, Piazzola sul Brenta, Italy
Rip:  mp3 @ 320 kbps 


Giovanni Paisiello (1740 - 1816)

Concerto in E-flat major for mandolin, strings, and harpsichord
1.  Allegro maestoso
2.  Larghetto
3.  Allegretto

Concerto in C major for mandolin, strings, and harpsichord
1.  Allegro
2.  Larghetto
3.  Allegro


Francesco Lecce (18th century)

Concerto in G major  for mandolin, strings, and harpsichord
1.  Allegro
2.  Largo
3.  Allegro balletto


Antonio Maria Giuliani (c. 1739 - 1831)

Concerto in E Major for two mandolins, viola, and orchestra
1.  Allegro
2.  Andante
3.  Allegro
